snippet.title: Amber Heard slams 'campaign' to remove her from Aquaman 2 amid Johnny Depp drama
snippet.description: has slammed a 'campaign' to have her removed from starring in the upcoming movie Aquaman 2.  The 34-year-old actress, who has been criticised by Johnny Depp fans after he lost his libel case against The Sun, remained confident that she would be returning to the role when the production begins.  It comes after fans launched a petition to have her axed that has continued to gain traction online and has received over 1 million signatures so far.  Despite cs to have her 'removed' from the film, Amber instead revealed that she was excited to return to the set to reprise her character Mera.  However, the movie is yet to be greenlit, which means that no casting has actuy been confirmed.    "I'm super excited about the amount of fan love and the amount of fan appreciation that Aquaman has acquired and that it has garnered so much excitement for Aquaman and Mera that it means we'll be coming back," Amber recently told Entertainment Weekly.  "I'm so excited to film that."  Amber went on to su ...
